00:12:52.390 --> 00:12:54.500
Each is half the intensity.

00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:59.200
So therefore, each creates a
photocurrent, which is n/2.

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.780
And since one laser beam,
which is a coherent state,

00:13:01.780 --> 00:13:04.470
gives two laser beams, which
are two coherent states,

00:13:04.470 --> 00:13:07.160
each of them has
a variance which

00:13:07.160 --> 00:13:09.550
is equal to the photon number.

00:13:09.550 --> 00:13:12.520
And this means, we have
Poissonian statistics.

00:13:12.520 --> 00:13:16.830
So we have n/2
photons in each beam.

00:13:16.830 --> 00:13:19.480
The standard deviation is
the square root of n/2.

00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:24.555
And the variance is n/2.

