00:22:46.220 --> 00:22:48.650
And what I try to sort of
challenge you today is,

00:22:48.650 --> 00:22:51.500
what happens to noise?

00:22:51.500 --> 00:22:56.060
So what I have to tell you
now is-- OK, got to hide this.

00:23:00.770 --> 00:23:03.580
The way you should look
at it very soon, I hope,

00:23:03.580 --> 00:23:07.680
is the following, that when
you split the coherent beam,

00:23:07.680 --> 00:23:09.630
you also split the noise.

00:23:09.630 --> 00:23:12.440
In other words, your
little uncertainty circle

00:23:12.440 --> 00:23:14.960
goes down in the amplitude
by square root of 2.

00:23:14.960 --> 00:23:18.080
It is split-- the reflection
coefficient of the beam spit

00:23:18.080 --> 00:23:21.940
and transmission coefficient
is 1 over square root 2.

00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:26.270
But what happens is, you
let in the vacuum here.

00:23:26.270 --> 00:23:29.710
And so, the vacuum comes into
the transmission coefficient

00:23:29.710 --> 00:23:31.750
of 1 over square root 2.

00:23:31.750 --> 00:23:34.990
So what I want to teach you
is that when we think back

00:23:34.990 --> 00:23:42.860
to this example and we had
this situation with a vacuum,

00:23:42.860 --> 00:23:47.290
yes, it looked to
us that we had n/2--

00:23:47.290 --> 00:23:54.050
so this was i1 plus
i2-- we had n/2 photons

00:23:54.050 --> 00:23:57.900
and the variance was n/2, it
looked completely Poissonian

00:23:57.900 --> 00:23:59.990
as if nothing has happened.

00:23:59.990 --> 00:24:03.860
But what you should understand
is, that the beam splitter

00:24:03.860 --> 00:24:08.400
has taken out-- in amplitude,
1 over square root 2,

00:24:08.400 --> 00:24:11.300
when I square it--
half of the noise out

00:24:11.300 --> 00:24:12.820
of the coherent state.

00:24:12.820 --> 00:24:15.360
But half of the vacuum
state was added.

00:24:15.360 --> 00:24:19.330
And half of the vacuum state
and half of the intrinsic noise

00:24:19.330 --> 00:24:23.130
of the coherent state give
you back this circle of unity.

00:24:23.130 --> 00:24:25.760
And you can pretty much
neglect all subtleties

00:24:25.760 --> 00:24:28.050
of the quantum field.

00:24:28.050 --> 00:24:32.150
But now, by messing
up with a vacuum,

00:24:32.150 --> 00:24:35.980
by squeezing the vacuum,
half of the shot noise

00:24:35.980 --> 00:24:37.300
comes from the beam splitter.

00:24:37.300 --> 00:24:40.510
It's a 50-50 beam splitter.

00:24:40.510 --> 00:24:43.740
But the other half comes
from the open part.

00:24:43.740 --> 00:24:47.890
But if you squeeze it strongly,
it's on the order epsilon.

00:24:47.890 --> 00:24:51.240
That means, it
doesn't contribute.

00:24:51.240 --> 00:25:02.350
And the correct answer is
now, we have-- just a second.

00:25:02.350 --> 00:25:05.110
It is linear or quadratic?

00:25:05.110 --> 00:25:08.170
Variance is quadratic.

00:25:08.170 --> 00:25:12.000
The correct answer is here,
because this is epsilon;

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:13.170
this is small.

00:25:13.170 --> 00:25:15.800
We only get half of the
noise we had before.

00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:17.420
We had n/2, and
now, we have n/4.

00:25:21.030 --> 00:25:21.530
OK.

00:25:30.170 --> 00:25:31.955
Now, we take exactly
the same situation.

00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:39.890
So the thought is that you
measure the fluctuation here

00:25:39.890 --> 00:25:44.410
and you have only half of them,
because this squeezed vacuum,

00:25:44.410 --> 00:25:47.860
you've squeezed out the
noise from the vacuum part.

00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:50.010
And since you have a
strong coherent state,

00:25:50.010 --> 00:25:53.000
everything which is sine
omega t doesn't matter.

00:25:53.000 --> 00:25:55.725
Cosine omega t is homodyned,
everything fluctuation

00:25:55.725 --> 00:25:57.590
and cosine omega t.

00:25:57.590 --> 00:26:01.600
When we measure, the intensity
is the square of phi,

00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:03.140
or it's a dagger a.

00:26:03.140 --> 00:26:05.490
And so if you measure
a quadratic quantity

00:26:05.490 --> 00:26:08.100
and we have a very
strong local oscillator,

00:26:08.100 --> 00:26:10.470
everything is projected
on cosine omega t.

00:26:10.470 --> 00:26:13.400
This is why only the
cosine omega t fluctuations

00:26:13.400 --> 00:26:15.830
of discrete statement are here.

00:26:15.830 --> 00:26:17.553
It's a strong local
oscillator limit.

00:26:21.120 --> 00:26:21.620
OK.

00:26:21.620 --> 00:26:24.390
Now, I hope you've
learned something.

00:26:24.390 --> 00:26:30.250
Next question is now, we
do exactly the same thing,

00:26:30.250 --> 00:26:33.350
but now we have
the two currents,

00:26:33.350 --> 00:26:38.390
and the question is, what
is the variance in i-plus?

00:26:38.390 --> 00:26:41.050
I add the two currents.

00:26:41.050 --> 00:26:42.000
What do I get?

00:26:44.830 --> 00:26:47.780
And I give you the
same choices as before.

00:26:47.780 --> 00:26:52.220
Just as a reminder,
when we did not squeeze,

00:26:52.220 --> 00:26:54.150
the variance was n.

00:26:54.150 --> 00:27:00.420
So the question is now, has
this squeezing done nothing,

00:27:00.420 --> 00:27:02.301
or has it reduced the variance?

00:27:02.301 --> 00:27:03.050
What is happening?

00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:29.390
The correct answer is C. It's n.

00:27:35.700 --> 00:27:38.690
And I will show you-- I owe
you a little bit of math now.

00:27:38.690 --> 00:27:42.050
But the way how you should
feel is the following.

00:27:42.050 --> 00:27:47.080
The noise of the coherent
oscillator is equally split.

00:27:47.080 --> 00:27:51.690
But the amplitude-- I mean,
you can say 50% go through, 50%

00:27:51.690 --> 00:27:52.610
go through here.

00:27:52.610 --> 00:27:54.410
And if you add the
two currents, you

00:27:54.410 --> 00:27:58.230
get back the full noise of
the original coherent state.

00:27:58.230 --> 00:28:00.410
You would say what
about the squeezing?

00:28:00.410 --> 00:28:02.550
Well, the issue
is the following.

00:28:02.550 --> 00:28:05.340
The squeezed light,
the squeezed vacuum,

00:28:05.340 --> 00:28:09.124
is reflected with a reflection
coefficient, which is minus 1

00:28:09.124 --> 00:28:10.040
over square root of 2.

00:28:10.040 --> 00:28:13.660
You know when you have two
beams reflected, by unitarity,

00:28:13.660 --> 00:28:16.030
it's necessary that
one has a negative,

00:28:16.030 --> 00:28:18.660
the other one has a positive
reflection coefficient.

00:28:18.660 --> 00:28:22.640
So therefore, you have
this squeezed vacuum

00:28:22.640 --> 00:28:25.030
appears in this arm
with a minus sign

00:28:25.030 --> 00:28:27.310
and this arm with a plus sign.

00:28:27.310 --> 00:28:29.640
And if you sum up
the two currents,

00:28:29.640 --> 00:28:33.870
you lose everything which is
related to the vacuum part.

00:28:33.870 --> 00:28:36.950
So when you measure
i1 plus i2, what

00:28:36.950 --> 00:28:40.190
came from the vacuum part
entered here with a minus sign,

00:28:40.190 --> 00:28:41.280
here with a plus sign.

00:28:41.280 --> 00:28:43.030
And therefore, you
[INAUDIBLE] what you've

00:28:43.030 --> 00:28:45.310
done at the vacuum part.

00:28:45.310 --> 00:28:48.820
This is when I told you
earlier, you measure i1 plus i2,

00:28:48.820 --> 00:28:51.840
and we all agreed,
the variance was n.

00:28:51.840 --> 00:28:53.760
And I said, well, this
is exactly the same

00:28:53.760 --> 00:28:57.120
if you put a photodiode-- big
photodiode-- behind the beam

00:28:57.120 --> 00:28:58.880
splitter or before
the beam splitter.

00:28:58.880 --> 00:29:01.020
The vacuum has not contributed.

00:29:01.020 --> 00:29:02.030
That's what it seems.

00:29:02.030 --> 00:29:04.920
But even if you squeeze
the vacuum, it cancels out.

00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:08.400
OK.

00:29:08.400 --> 00:29:10.420
Now, the obvious
next question-- but I

00:29:10.420 --> 00:29:12.270
think I've given
you the answer--

00:29:12.270 --> 00:29:17.270
is what happens when we
now measure the difference,

00:29:17.270 --> 00:29:20.700
i1 minus i2?

00:29:20.700 --> 00:29:26.800
Again, without squeezing,
the variance was n.

00:29:26.800 --> 00:29:30.350
So now, we measure i1
minus i2, and what happens?

00:29:45.780 --> 00:29:47.760
OK.

00:29:47.760 --> 00:29:50.190
The correct answer is this.

00:29:58.025 --> 00:30:01.200
Well, when I say 0, it's
always epsilon squared terms

00:30:01.200 --> 00:30:01.910
which I neglect.

00:30:01.910 --> 00:30:03.780
I just assume strong squeezing.

00:30:03.780 --> 00:30:06.390
I mean, I just want to give you
the most conceptional problem.

00:30:06.390 --> 00:30:08.840
What happens is the following.

00:30:08.840 --> 00:30:10.264
And I will show
you the equation.

00:30:17.360 --> 00:30:21.520
The noise of the coherent
state is split equally.

00:30:21.520 --> 00:30:25.510
So we have a delta a--
a is the field operator,

00:30:25.510 --> 00:30:28.970
or the quadrature operator
here-- and a delta a here.

00:30:28.970 --> 00:30:31.470
And therefore, the
original shot noise

00:30:31.470 --> 00:30:34.850
is common mode, because the
reflection and transmission

00:30:34.850 --> 00:30:36.310
coefficients are the same.

00:30:36.310 --> 00:30:39.000
And if you subtract the
current, you completely

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:41.730
get rid of all noise,
which was originally

00:30:41.730 --> 00:30:43.230
associated with
your coherent state.

00:30:46.460 --> 00:30:51.446
Now, what happens is
the small noise we get,

00:30:51.446 --> 00:30:53.320
but now, we have to
consider the vacuum part.

00:30:53.320 --> 00:30:55.820
But what comes in on the
same quadrature component

00:30:55.820 --> 00:31:00.510
point on the vacuum
tube is strongly split.

00:31:00.510 --> 00:31:06.800
And because the beam
splitter has different signs

00:31:06.800 --> 00:31:10.260
for reflection and transmission,
the noise is anti-correlated.

00:31:10.260 --> 00:31:12.230
And if you take
the difference, you

00:31:12.230 --> 00:31:19.160
will actually measure the noise
of the input of the open part

00:31:19.160 --> 00:31:27.110
of the beam splitter, which
would mean, in terms of order

00:31:27.110 --> 00:31:31.400
epsilon-- I didn't work it out.

00:31:31.400 --> 00:31:33.290
I think it's epsilon squared.

00:31:33.290 --> 00:31:34.760
But it's a power of epsilon.

00:31:40.540 --> 00:31:44.750
So anyway, it seems your
intuition fails here.

