00:42:13.940 --> 00:42:16.320
let's assume you have
a piece of glass,

00:42:16.320 --> 00:42:19.040
which has some coating on it.

00:42:19.040 --> 00:42:24.850
One beam is reflected when
it goes from the vacuum

00:42:24.850 --> 00:42:26.410
to material interface.

00:42:26.410 --> 00:42:28.445
The other one is reflected
from the material

00:42:28.445 --> 00:42:29.610
to vacuum interface.

00:42:29.610 --> 00:42:31.953
AUDIENCE: So then, it depends
on which face of the beam

00:42:31.953 --> 00:42:33.030
that will be put which--?

00:42:33.030 --> 00:42:35.390
PROFESSOR: But one thing
